  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nIf User1 has synced devices and declines request for outgoing transaction from User2, or User2 shares address for incoming transaction from User1 in 1-1 chat, the status of this commands is updated only on one of the synced devices (User1). On the second synced device status doesn't update. (**Case 1**)\n\nAlso if User1 requests transaction from one of the synced devices, this request doesn't appear on the second device. (**Case 2**)\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\nTransaction status is updated on both synchronized devices; the transaction messages themselves are shown. \n\n#### Actual behavior\n\n![Снимок экрана 2020-08-05 в 5 15 54 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/89430771-6542a780-d73f-11ea-932c-3b734bd423b1.png)\n\n### Reproduction\n\n#### Case 1\n\nUser2:\n- Open 1-1 chat with User1\n- Open transaction dialog and request transaction\n\nUser1:\n- Sync two devices\n- Decline request from User2 on Device1\n- Open 1-1 chat with User2 on Device2\n\n#### Case 2\n\n- User1 sync two devices\n- Open 1-1 chat with User2 on Device1\n- Open transaction dialog and request transaction\n- Open 1-1 chat with User2 on Device2\n\n### Additional Information\n\n- Status version: Release 1.5\n- Operating System: Android 10; iOS13",
